In a large mixing bowl, combine all of the ingredients thoroughly. Cover loosely with a linen cloth and let rest in a warm Spot (about 70 degrees F) for at least 10 to 12 hours. or up to 24 hours. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. Lightly grease an 8-by-4-by-4-inch loaf pan and dust with cornmeal. Pour the batter into the prepared pan and smooth evenly with a spatula. Sprinkle with cornmeal and sea salt. Bake for 1 hour and 45 minutes. until firm to the touch and a toothpick inserted into the center Comes out clean.